Feature: Google search in categories with filters

  Scenario: Search for "prowly" with no date filter
    Given I am on the Google homepage
    When I search for "prowly"
    And I do not apply any date filter
    Then I should see search results containing "prowly"
    And the results should be sorted by Google's default ranking algorithm

  Scenario: Search for "prowly" in "Videos" with "Short (0-4 min)" filter 
    Given I am on the Google homepage
    When I search for "prowly"
    And I filter results by "Videos"
    And I filter results by "Short (0-4 min)"
    Then I should see videos related to "prowly"
    And duration of each video should be 4 minutes or less

  Scenario: Search for "prowly" with a filter for results from the past week
    Given I am on the Google homepage
    When I search for "prowly"
    And I filter results by "Past week"
    Then I should see results related to "prowly"
    And each result should contain a publication date
    And each result should be published 7 days ago at most